From 913ec3c996cbe6fad0cdda68a10a93374437110b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Harshitha Prem <hprem@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Sat, 26 Jul 2025 20:20:11 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 2/8] QSDK: CP: hostapd: ATF: Add atf_group helpers

Implement Airtime Fairness (ATF) algorithm to work
based on entities such as group configs because, once
algorithm is complete based on the configs provided by user,
it will be sent as group config to the driver.

User can provide following level of configs for airtime fairness:
	1. ssid config - per ssid airtime allocation
	2. ssid group config - consist of one or more ssid with airtime
allocation
	3. peer config - per station config for airtime allocation
within group/ssid.

When ssid group is enabled, ssid config would not be possible.

An ATF group consist of one or more SSIDs. By default,
during initialization of atf_algo, create a default
group which would consist of all the bss in the iface which
are not configured by user explicitly.

add helper apis for group allocation, deletion which
would be later used by the algorithm. Also, add parsing
of hostapd config parsed.

Also, add support for below config options in hostapd.conf:

atf_offload_config - this is the config file which would
have all the airtime related configurations specific to
per ssid, per group, and per peer.

commitatf - this is used for dynamic enable and disable of
ATF configuration per radio.

atfssidgroup - this is used to enable the ssid grouping feature.

Add support to parse atf group specific config in atf_offload_config
file:
To add an ATF group - it would have set of group configuration
consisting of group name, ssid names that are in the group,
airtime of the group.
Here, the airtime would be in the range of 0 - 100%.

There can be multiple group configurations

atf-group=group1
atf-group-ssid=ssid1,ssid2
atf-group-airtime=30

...
atf-group=group2
atf-group-ssid=ssid3
atf-group-airtime=20

To delete an ATF group - use below config with group name.
atf-del-group=group2

Signed-off-by: Harshitha Prem <hprem@qti.qualcomm.com>
